<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="319" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,188,213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
MALE. Body robust and short, especially pronotal disc, propodeal disc and metasoma (
<figureCitation box="[1350,1419,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4 Trichiscus noorti sp. nov.; 1. Habitus; 2. Head, dorsal view; 3. Mandible, lateral view; 4. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 5. T. copelandi sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. T. ohli sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 7 – 9 T. noorti sp. nov.; 7. Forewing, dorsal view; 8. Metasoma, lateral view; 9. Metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228358/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">
Fig. 
<number box="[1406,1419,188,212]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Antenna with eleven flagellomeres (
<figureCitation box="[561,632,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4 Trichiscus noorti sp. nov.; 1. Habitus; 2. Head, dorsal view; 3. Mandible, lateral view; 4. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 5. T. copelandi sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. T. ohli sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 7 – 9 T. noorti sp. nov.; 7. Forewing, dorsal view; 8. Metasoma, lateral view; 9. Metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228358/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">
Fig. 
<number box="[615,632,224,248]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Mandible with three apical teeth, upper one wide, blunt and inclined, median one sharpened, lower one sharpened and large (
<figureCitation box="[782,852,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4 Trichiscus noorti sp. nov.; 1. Habitus; 2. Head, dorsal view; 3. Mandible, lateral view; 4. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 5. T. copelandi sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. T. ohli sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 7 – 9 T. noorti sp. nov.; 7. Forewing, dorsal view; 8. Metasoma, lateral view; 9. Metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228358/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">
Fig. 
<number box="[836,852,260,284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Mandible with upper margin very thick, followed by front keel. Clypeus wholly prominent forward, its median lobe not well outlined, median area elevated (
<figureCitation box="[1353,1423,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4 Trichiscus noorti sp. nov.; 1. Habitus; 2. Head, dorsal view; 3. Mandible, lateral view; 4. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 5. T. copelandi sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. T. ohli sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 7 – 9 T. noorti sp. nov.; 7. Forewing, dorsal view; 8. Metasoma, lateral view; 9. Metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228358/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">
Fig. 
<number box="[1406,1423,296,320]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Occipital carina conspicuous dorsally, weak or absent ventrally. Palpal formula 
<number box="[1135,1153,332,357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="6.0">6</number>
: 
<number box="[1158,1174,332,357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="3.0">3</number>
. Notaulus incomplete posteriorly on mesoscutum (
<figureCitation box="[469,538,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4 Trichiscus noorti sp. nov.; 1. Habitus; 2. Head, dorsal view; 3. Mandible, lateral view; 4. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 5. T. copelandi sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. T. ohli sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 7 – 9 T. noorti sp. nov.; 7. Forewing, dorsal view; 8. Metasoma, lateral view; 9. Metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228358/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">
Fig. 
<number box="[521,538,368,392]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Parapsidal furrow complete (
<figureCitation box="[881,951,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4 Trichiscus noorti sp. nov.; 1. Habitus; 2. Head, dorsal view; 3. Mandible, lateral view; 4. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 5. T. copelandi sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. T. ohli sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 7 – 9 T. noorti sp. nov.; 7. Forewing, dorsal view; 8. Metasoma, lateral view; 9. Metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228358/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">
Fig. 
<number box="[934,951,368,392]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Scutellar disc usually rounded posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[159,228,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4 Trichiscus noorti sp. nov.; 1. Habitus; 2. Head, dorsal view; 3. Mandible, lateral view; 4. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 5. T. copelandi sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. T. ohli sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 7 – 9 T. noorti sp. nov.; 7. Forewing, dorsal view; 8. Metasoma, lateral view; 9. Metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228358/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,228,404,428]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
), sometimes sharpened (Fig.s 
<number box="[570,616,404,429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
). Forewing with basal vein reaching subcostal vein far from stigma (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4 Trichiscus noorti sp. nov.; 1. Habitus; 2. Head, dorsal view; 3. Mandible, lateral view; 4. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 5. T. copelandi sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. T. ohli sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 7 – 9 T. noorti sp. nov.; 7. Forewing, dorsal view; 8. Metasoma, lateral view; 9. Metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228358/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,167,440,464]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Metasoma with tergal process on tergite III (
<figureCitation box="[681,782,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4 Trichiscus noorti sp. nov.; 1. Habitus; 2. Head, dorsal view; 3. Mandible, lateral view; 4. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 5. T. copelandi sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. T. ohli sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 7 – 9 T. noorti sp. nov.; 7. Forewing, dorsal view; 8. Metasoma, lateral view; 9. Metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228358/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">
Figs 
<number box="[737,782,440,464]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8–9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Metasomal tergite I longer than II (
<figureCitation box="[1191,1293,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4 Trichiscus noorti sp. nov.; 1. Habitus; 2. Head, dorsal view; 3. Mandible, lateral view; 4. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 5. T. copelandi sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. T. ohli sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 7 – 9 T. noorti sp. nov.; 7. Forewing, dorsal view; 8. Metasoma, lateral view; 9. Metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228358/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">
Figs 
<number box="[1247,1293,440,464]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8–9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Metasomal tergite II shorter than III, its posterior margin strongly excavated (
<figureCitation box="[917,1023,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4 Trichiscus noorti sp. nov.; 1. Habitus; 2. Head, dorsal view; 3. Mandible, lateral view; 4. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 5. T. copelandi sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. T. ohli sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 7 – 9 T. noorti sp. nov.; 7. Forewing, dorsal view; 8. Metasoma, lateral view; 9. Metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228358/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">
Figs 
<number box="[977,1023,476,500]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8–9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergal process consisting of some paralleled rows of setae placed on anterior third of lateral surface (
<figureCitation box="[921,992,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1925,1947]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[207,1377,193,1909]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 9. 1 – 4 Trichiscus noorti sp. nov.; 1. Habitus; 2. Head, dorsal view; 3. Mandible, lateral view; 4. Mesosoma, dorsal view. 5. T. copelandi sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. T. ohli sp. nov., mesosoma, dorsal view. 7 – 9 T. noorti sp. nov.; 7. Forewing, dorsal view; 8. Metasoma, lateral view; 9. Metasoma, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228358/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="319">
Fig. 
<number box="[976,992,512,536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="319" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypopygeal median stalk very wide, apex usually rounded, lateral stalk conspicuous, posterior margin emarginated in many species. Paramere with apical surface folded into outer and inner laminae. Basiparamere distinctly separated from basivolsella on ventral side; apical surface horizontal, angled inward. Digitus with hypertrophied membranous ramous giving rise from out surface of basal area. Basivolsella with inner border thickened. Aedeagus divided into dorsal body and ventral ramus. Aedeagal apodeme short. Base of aedeagus covered by dorsal diamond-shaped lamina. Genital ring very wide laterally. Basal ring absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
